    {
      "id": "CVE-2026-5398",
      "publishedDate": "2026-04-22T02:23:56.767Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-04-22T02:23:56.767Z",
      "description": "The implementation of TIOCNOTTY failed to clear a back-pointer from the structure representing the controlling terminal to the calling process' session.  If the invoking process then exits, the terminal structure may end up containing a pointer to freed memory.\n\nA malicious process can abuse the dangling pointer to grant itself root privileges.",
